#USAGE OF miRPV

Once all the tools and dependence is install correctly then pipeline should be ready to use.

**Just run from the miRPV folder:
	$bash miRPV.sh (After doing this it will ask for fasta file name or the sample which you are going to use. Sample file should be present where the miRPV.sh script is there)
		<Inpute the fasta file name> (Give the fasta file name)
		Test.fa (Then press Enter)

This will analyse the sample with different tools, it will take time according the sample size. You will get to know when your sample run is finish when a train passes by that time you get to know that the pipeline has run without any error. If any error occur examine the error and try to resolve it. 

The new Directory is created Output directory in which five folder's are created with each tools output the final result of miRPV can found in the miRPV_output folder where you can see pdf file.

**For Feature extration 
	Copy the Hairplendex.txt file from output/hairplendex directory to Software/HAirplendex/file follow the command in the README file and you will get the features of Pri-miRNA

